    id: "6604c919-0c64-4dbd-a463-693294e9f718",
    description: `Tafsir Ibn Kathir (Urdu) - Complete Set is the definitive Urdu translation of Tafsir al-Quran al-Azim by the eminent scholar Hafiz Imaduddin Ismail ibn Umar ibn Kathir (701–774 AH), widely regarded as one of the most authoritative and comprehensive Quranic exegeses in the Islamic scholarly tradition. This complete 10-volume set presents the full Urdu rendering of Ibn Kathir's masterwork, which systematically explains every verse of the Holy Quran through authentic Hadith, statements of the Sahabah and Tabi'in, and scholarly commentary grounded in the principles of Tafsir bil-Ma'thur (interpretation based on transmitted sources). The Urdu translation maintains the scholarly precision of the original Arabic while making this essential reference work accessible to the vast Urdu-speaking Muslim population across South Asia and beyond.

Ibn Kathir's methodology in this Tafsir is distinguished by its strict adherence to interpreting the Quran through the Quran itself, through authentic Hadith, and through the understanding of the earliest generations of Muslims. For each verse, he first presents other Quranic verses that provide context or clarification, then relevant authenticated Hadith that explain the verse's meaning, followed by the interpretations of major Sahabah including Ibn Abbas, Ibn Masud, and Ubayy ibn Ka'b, and finally the opinions of leading Tabi'i scholars. This layered approach gives readers a comprehensive understanding of each passage that is firmly rooted in the most reliable sources of Islamic knowledge. The Tafsir gives special attention to verses related to Islamic law (Ayat al-Ahkam), providing detailed discussions of the rulings derived from them, and to stories of the Prophets (Qasas al-Anbiya), presenting them with their full historical context and lessons.

This Urdu complete set encompasses all 30 Paras (Juz) of the Quran across its 10 volumes, with each volume covering approximately three Juz. The translation uses clear, scholarly Urdu that preserves the technical terminology of Islamic sciences while remaining accessible to educated general readers. Each volume includes detailed introductions that discuss the themes of the Surahs contained within, their reasons for revelation (Asbab al-Nuzul), and their relationship to preceding and succeeding Surahs. The set features the complete Arabic text of the Quran alongside the Urdu commentary, with key terms and difficult phrases annotated for clarity. Cross-references to related verses and Hadith are provided throughout, enabling readers to trace themes across the entire Quran. This edition has been published with careful editorial oversight, with corrections verified against authoritative Arabic manuscripts of the original Tafsir. It serves as an essential reference for scholars, students of Islamic studies, Imams and Khateebs, and any serious reader seeking a deeply authentic understanding of the Quranic message.`
